This repository contains MATLAB scripts corresponding to different stages of the EEG analysis pipeline for subject 13AR.

🔹 Core Analysis Files

1. psd_preprocessing
Data loaded from FieldTrip .mat structure
Occipital channels selected:
O1, Oz, O2, POz, PO3, PO4, PO7, PO8, Iz
Signals averaged across channels

2. psd_compare_conditions_13AR.mat
Computes and visualizes Power Spectral Density (PSD) across conditions
Compares:
Eyes Closed (EC)
Eyes Open (EO)
Grating (G)
Helps identify frequency-domain differences (especially alpha band)

3. alpha_power_13AR.mat
Extracts alpha-band power (8–12 Hz) across trials
Generates:
Alpha power distributions
Boxplots across conditions
Used to validate physiological behavior (EC > EO)

4. condition_classification_13AR.mat
Performs classification analysis using band-power features
Evaluates:
Within-condition accuracy
Cross-condition generalization
Used to assess separability of brain states

5. variability_analysis_13AR.mat
Computes variance of features across conditions
Quantifies:
Stability vs variability of neural responses
Provides a first estimate of representation consistency

6. cii_analysis_13AR.mat
Implements Context Invariance Index (CII) using:
Multi-band features (delta–beta)
Computes:
Similarity matrix
Global CII
Core metric for cross-condition invariance

7. cii_alpha_only_13AR.mat
Computes CII using only alpha-band features
Enables comparison between:
Low-dimensional (alpha)
High-dimensional (full-band)
Highlights importance of feature richness

🔹 Phase-wise Analysis Files

8. phase2_temporal_cii_13AR.mat
Performs temporal stability analysis
Compares:
EC1 vs EC2
EO1 vs EO2
G1 vs G2
Computes:
Alpha CII
Full-band CII
Validates consistency over time

9. phase3_meditation_analysis_13AR.mat
Performs full 8-condition analysis
Generates:
8×8 similarity matrix
Meditation vs baseline comparison
Computes:
Global CII for meditation vs baseline
Core file for final results and conclusions


How Files Connect (Pipeline Flow)
PSD → Alpha Power → Variability → Classification → CII → Temporal Stability → Meditation Analysis

Recommended Execution Order

Run the scripts in the following order:

psd_compare_conditions_13AR
alpha_power_13AR
variability_analysis_13AR
condition_classification_13AR
cii_analysis_13AR
cii_alpha_only_13AR
phase2_temporal_cii_13AR
phase3_meditation_analysis_13AR

What Each File Contributes:

File	          Purpose	                  Output
Pre-process     Data check                Spectral plots
PSD	            Frequency analysis	      Spectral plots
Alpha	          Band-specific analysis	  Boxplots
Variability	    Stability measure	        Variance
Classification	Separability	            Accuracy
CII	            Invariance metric	        Similarity
Phase 2	        Temporal validation	      Stability
Phase 3	        Final analysis	          Meditation effect
